      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It's great that your skin is looking better, but you should never stop antibiotics just because you feel fine. Stopping early can let the infection come back stronger, and the bacteria might be resistant to the weaker dose you're about to use. Please call your doctor or pharmacist immediately to discuss a proper tapering schedule, or if you're feeling unsure, just keep taking the full course until they tell you to stop.",
      "source": "target",
